[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm trying to understand if to cover the call site, code must execute during the native image build, particularly focusing on static initializers of test classes. It seems like classes are initialized at build time but not generally test classes. Still, JUnit discovery might load tests during the image build without executing test methods. I’m curious if the dynamic-access report includes recorded calls from native image execution too, so it might be worth checking the documentation for clarity.
